Name: acute conjunctivitis
Definition: A non-suppurative otitis media and eustachian tube disorder which is persistent and long-lasting.
Synonym: Septicemia due to hemophilus influenzae [H. influenzae]

Name: papillary conjunctivitis
Definition: A blepharitis that is characterized by the dual combination of conjunctivitis with blepharitis.

Name: chronic conjunctivitis
Definition: A systemic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in human body of immunocompromised individuals

Name: bacterial conjunctivitis
Definition: A bacterial conjuctivitis that is characterized by pain and tenderness in the eyeball and conjuctival discharge.

Name: rosacea conjunctivitis
Definition: A bacterial conjuctivitis that is characterized by pain and tenderness in the eyeball and conjuctival discharge.
